  ],
  "rationale": "<p>Choice A is correct. It&rsquo;s given that an object&rsquo;s kinetic energy, in joules, is equal to the product of one-half the object&rsquo;s mass, in kilograms, and the square of the object&rsquo;s speed, in meters per second. This relationship can be represented by the equation <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"K equals, one half m v squared\"></span>, where <span class=\"italic\">K</span> is the kinetic energy, <span class=\"italic\">m </span>is the mass, and <span class=\"italic\">v </span>is the speed. Substituting a mass of 4 kilograms for <span class=\"italic\">m </span>and a kinetic energy of 18 joules for <span class=\"italic\">K </span>results in the equation <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"18 equals, one half times 4, times v squared\"></span>, or <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"18 equals, 2 v squared\"></span>. Dividing both sides of this equation by 2 yields <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"9 equals, v squared\"></span>. Taking the square root of both sides yields <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"v equals, negative 3\"></span> and <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"v equals 3\"></span>. Since speed can&rsquo;t be expressed as a negative number, the speed of the object is 3 meters per second.<p>Choice B is incorrect and may result from computation errors. Choice C is incorrect. This is the value of <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"v squared  \"></span> rather than <span class=\"italic\">v</span>. Choice D is incorrect. This is the value of <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"4 v squared  \"></span> rather than <span class=\"italic\">v</span>.</p><p>&nbsp;</p></p>\n",
